      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HEZA PUNK ROCKER NZ (10) finished second last start over 1800m at Globe Derby Park, beaten 4 metres, after also filling a minor placing at the previous appearance over 2230m there. No favours expected from this draw but rates a big chance if anywhere near his best. MY ULTIMATE JIMMY NZ (8) finished ninth at Maryborough two starts back then was back in the frame at his latest appearance over 2190m at at this track, beaten 13 metres into second after being up on the pace. May need luck at some stage extracting from the inside of the second row but that latest effort is good enough to put him right in the finish. NEVS DREAM (1) is one of the main contenders after winning her past two starts, the latest at this circuit two weeks ago. Difficult to ignore that sort of form. TOUGH AINT ENOUGH (7) is the best of the rest after finishing third over 2190m at this course last time out.",
